ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: The code that identifies a type of study protocol based upon the intent of the study's activities.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

Concepts.definition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

ValueMeaning.administrativeNotes: 1/25/23 added alt name for ticket number CADSR0001948 for CCTG cjl.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Studies which are secondary to another study.

Concepts.definition: A study that is secondary to another study.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Fundamental research designed to obtain or increase general scientific knowledge, performed without the goal of developing a direct application intended to solve a specific problem.

Concepts.definition: Fundamental research designed to obtain or increase general scientific knowledge.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A type of study that tests for a relationship between a condition and a potential causal factor of the condition.

Concepts.definition: A type of study that tests for a relationship between a condition and a potential causal factor of the condition.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A type of study protocol designed to evaluate intervention(s) aimed at identifying disease and condition.

Concepts.definition: A type of study designed to evaluate method(s) aimed at identifying a disease or condition.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Clinical studies testing the efficacy of devices, techniques, procedures, or tests for earlier diagnosis of disease.

Concepts.definition: Clinical studies testing the efficacy of devices, techniques, procedures, or tests for earlier diagnosis of disease.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The study of human populations to identify causes of disease and factors determining and influencing the frequency and distribution of disease, injury, and other health related events.

Concepts.definition: The study of human populations to identify causes of disease and factors determining and influencing the frequency and distribution of disease, injury, and other health related events.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The integration of epidemiologic, sociological, economic, and other analytic sciences in the study of health services. Health services research is usually concerned with relationships between need, demand, supply, use, and outcome of health services. The aim of the research is evaluation, particularly in terms of structure, process, output, and outcome. (From Last, Dictionary of Epidemiology, 2d ed)

Concepts.definition: A multidisciplinary field of inquiry that examines the costs, quality, accessibility, delivery, organization, financing, and outcomes of health care services.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Studies among cancer patients and healthy populations that involve no intervention or alteration in the status of the participants.

Concepts.definition: Studies among cancer patients and healthy populations that involve no intervention or alteration in the status of the participants.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The study of the end results of health services, with the intention of providing scientific evidence relating to the value of the decisions made by all who participate in the health care process.

Concepts.definition: The study of the end results of health services, with the intention of providing scientific evidence relating to the value of the decisions made by all who participate in the health care process.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A type of study designed to identify actions necessary to permanently eliminate or reduce the long-term risk to human life as a result of a particular medication or treatment regimen.

Concepts.definition: A type of study protocol designed to evaluate intervention(s) for disease prevention.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Clinical studies testing the efficacy of devices, techniques, procedures, or tests for the purpose of detecting the presence of disease, usually before there are any symptoms.

Concepts.definition: Clinical studies testing the efficacy of devices, techniques, procedures, or tests for the purpose of detecting the presence of disease, usually before there are any symptoms.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Clinical studies intended to improve the comfort and quality of life for the patient using drugs, nutritional, dietary, behavioral or other interventions.

Concepts.definition: Clinical studies intended to improve the comfort and quality of life for the patient using drugs, nutritional, dietary, behavioral or other interventions.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A type of study protocol designed to evaluate intervention(s) for treatment of disease, syndrome or condition.

Concepts.definition: A type of study protocol designed to evaluate intervention(s) for disease treatment.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: the management of a research protocol and its case report forms.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Type; a subdivision of a particular kind of thing.

Concepts.definition: Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.
